## Resolved mutable: browser-sessionid-unstable

PARTIALLY confirmed as mechanism but the dominant axis is CWD not sessionId: sessionProfileDir(cwd, claudeSessionId) = path.join(cwd, '.gm', 'browser-profile-'+slug(sid)). Across worktrees the cwd differs (wf_b7706de2-add-5 vs add-8), so even with an identical sid each worktree resolves a DISTINCT profile dir under its own tree and launches its own chromium. The browser-ports.json registry also lives under browserStateDir(cwd)=<cwd>/.gm/exec-spool, so each worktree has its OWN ports registry and cannot see siblings' live browsers. Witness: live distinct user-data-dirs both ending browser-profile-default but rooted in different worktrees.